Using the pipe |&gt;
The |&gt; operator allows you to take the output of one function and feed it directly into the first argument of the next function. Using the |&gt; makes it easier to read your code, which is a good thing.

c(-1, -1, 1, 1) |&gt;
  abs() |&gt;
  sum()

